lwear"},{"type":"entry","text":"children’s garments 童装","headword":"children’s garments"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"text","text":"有趣的小词shirt"},{"type":"text","text":"1. Keep your shirt on.你别着急。"},{"type":"entry","text":"Keep one’s shirt on意为“别着急，保持冷静”。比如，你和朋友要","headword":"Keep one’s shirt on"},{"type":"text","text":"出去逛街，她总是催你Aren’t you ready to go yet? （你还没准备好"},{"type":"text","text":"吗？），你就可以说Keep your shirt on.I’m coming. （别着急嘛。我就"},{"type":"text","text":"来。）"},{"type":"text","text":"2. He lost his shirt. 他输光了。"},{"type":"entry","text":"Lose one’s shirt的意思是“输掉大笔钱，输得精光”。例如：He lost","headword":"Lose one’s shirt"},{"type":"text","text":"his shirt in a card game. （他在一场牌局中输了个精光。）这个表达一"},{"type":"text","text":"般指在赛马或赌博中把所带的钱输光了，有时也可指由于进行大的投"},{"type":"text","text":"资，把自己的全部财产赔光了，例如：Joe lost his shirt on the stock"},{"type":"text","text":"market. （乔在股票市场上赔光了。）"}]}]}